Paper: hep-th/0109046

Date: 2001-09-06

Title: Summing the derivative expansion of the effective action

Authors: Eduard Masso (UAB, Barcelona) and Francesc Rota (UAB, Barcelona)

Comments: 14 pages, no figures. Latex-file. Reference added

Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys. B620 (2002) 566-578

The derivative expansion of the effective action is a perturbativedevelopment in derivatives of the fields. The expansion breaks down when someof the derivatives are too large. We show how to sum exactly the first andsecond derivatives and treat perturbatively derivatives higher than second.